snippet.textDisplay: The young guys don’t owe Iggy any respect.  He hasn’t shown any interest in their success so I can’t blame the young guys for not caring.  Imagine if someone was brought in to your office, given a leadership role, and all they did was sit around, drink coffee, and talk about how they didn’t want to work there.  Would you be upset?  Would you show that person, even if they are your superior, any respect?  Same thing here.  Doesn’t matter the initials behind the name, the awards and accolades, if they aren’t there to support you then who gives a flip.  Iggy doesn’t deserve their respect just because he’s older.  And c’mon, Iggy is a great role player who landed in an ideal situation where he could play behind Steph, Klay, and Draymond.  We’re not talking about an all time great or HOF’er here.

snippet.textDisplay:
True fans of the Memphis Grizzlies are extremely proud of the future of their franchise, Ja Morant, for co-signing the comment of teammate Dillon Brooks. By going back at the popular all-time great and fan favorite Step, the rookie Ja is showing early signs of leadership reminiscent of Isiah "Zeke' Thomas by putting the basketball world on notice of their team's frustration with Iggy and anyone else who is, or will be on their roster, and not willing to be all in as a teammate working towards delivering a championship to their organization and city.

Edit: I'm no Grizzlies fan, nor do I have any ties to Tennessee.
